local TypeText = require "actions/TypeText" local Serial = require "actions/Serial" local Spawn = require "actions/Spawn" local Ease = require "actions/Ease" local Do = require "actions/Do" local YieldUntil = require "actions/YieldUntil" local BlockPlayer = require "actions/BlockPlayer" local Menu = require "actions/Menu"
local Layout = require "util/Layout" local Transform = require "util/Transform"
return function(self, player, prevState) if player.onSubLocation == self then return end player.onSubLocation = self
player.knotholeCallback = function(key) if player.onSubLocation == self and not self.scene.sceneMgr.transitioning and key == "x" then self.scene:run(BlockPlayer { Menu { layout = Layout { {Layout.Text("Enter Knothole?"), selectable = false}, {Layout.Text("Yes"), choose = function(menu) menu:close() self.scene.player:run { menu, Do(function() self.scene:changeScene{map="knothole", hint="fromworldmap", fadeOutSpeed = 0.5} self.scene:removeHandler("keytriggered", player.knotholeCallback) end) } end}, {Layout.Text("No"), choose = function(menu) menu:close() end} }, cancellable = true, transform = Transform(love.graphics.getWidth()/2, love.graphics.getHeight()/2 + 30), selectedRow = 2 } }) end end self.scene:addHandler("keytriggered", player.knotholeCallback)
self.typeText = TypeText( Transform(50, 470), {255, 255, 255, 0}, FontCache.TechnoSmall, "Knothole", 100 ) self.scene:run(Spawn(Serial { self.typeText, Ease(self.typeText.color, 4, 255, 1), YieldUntil(function() return self.state ~= self.STATE_TOUCHING end), Ease(self.typeText.color, 4, 0, 1) })) end
return function(self, player) if player.onSubLocation == self then player.onSubLocation = nil self.scene:removeHandler("keytriggered", player.deatheggCallback) end end
